These threads are directly managed by the operating system kernel.

Characteristics:
Managed by OS
Kernel schedules threads
True parallel execution possible

Advantages:
✔ Better CPU utilization
✔ True multithreading
✔ One blocked thread does not stop others

Disadvantages:
✘ Slower creation than user threads
✘ More overhead (kernel involvement)

Examples:
Supported by operating systems like Microsoft Windows and Linux.
